On August 18, 2020, President Donald J. Trump issued a proclamation to commemorate the 100th anniversary of the ratification of the 19th Amendment to the United States Constitution. This amendment secured the right to vote for women and was a significant step towards achieving a more equal society. The proclamation acknowledges the efforts of suffragists and advocates for women's rights who fought tirelessly for this milestone in American history. It also highlights the economic, political, and social contributions that women have made to the nation. The proclamation emphasizes President Trump's commitment to building on these accomplishments and empowering women and girls to achieve their fullest potential. It mentions initiatives such as the Women's Global Development and Prosperity Initiative and the Strategy on Women, Peace, and Security. The proclamation also recognizes the importance of combatting sex trafficking and prioritizing the safety and well-being of women and girls. President Trump's administration has implemented policies to enhance freedom and create opportunities for women and working families, such as the 2017 Tax Cuts and Jobs Act, increased funding for child care, and paid parental leave for federal employees. The proclamation concludes by paying tribute to the women throughout history who fought for equality and recommitting to upholding the Constitution to allow all Americans to pursue their dreams and reach their full potential.